Today I heard on the radio a Helb Alpert recording for the first time in
many years.  Playing along with the vinyl in 6-8 grade helped my playing
develop greatly.  Sure glad I expanded my tastes shortly after to Kenton,
Rich etc.

Anyway, I was wondering, how does one describe Alpert's sound?  Compact?  It
seems there are no overtones -also the sound just stops--no echo, resonance.
Still, the notes were solid and in tune.  Most of his stuff was short
staccato notes.  Nothing with a line over it.  What terms are used to
describe a sound like his?  (and for all you wise guys out there-remember
the post a week back from someone for now swearing ;).
Steve
