I dunno about &quot;groomed for Hollywood,&quot; but Albert is an incredible
musician, composer, producer, and businessman. Don't forget, he wrote
all his hits; in '66, his albums held the number 1 and 2 slots (over
the Beatles at 3 and 4) for a month, and Albert, in '66, had four
albums in the top ten (which no one has matched), and five in the top
20 (which put him in the Guinness Book o' Records). He even had major
hits as a vocalist; &quot;This Guy's In Love With You&quot; was a number 1
single &amp; album in '68. It even has a very pretty, dark trumpet solo.
Listen to the glissandos and quarter-tones... listen how much is
packed into about eight bars.

The guy has sold something like 72 million records; that's gotta be
more than even Mickey.

As a composer and producer, Albert had hits with Jan &amp; Dean and others
dating back to '58, long before the Tijuana Brass formed. A&amp;M was
among the most innovative of the major labels, and Albert started it
all in a garage. The guy is so much bigger than &quot;just&quot; his trumpet
playing that he deserves fair consideration.

I like his playing. And I admit, early stuff like &quot;Lonely Bull&quot; and
&quot;Mexican Shuffle,&quot; that I heard as a little kid, turned me on to the
trumpet. Even though I can name a dozen players I like a little better
as players, there's hardly a dozen people in the music industry who've
done what Albert has.

I'm not too keen on his paintings, though.  ;-)

